history.text: HI! Seen any good movies lately?
Actually, I just recently saw John Wick, the second one. What about you?
Ah, Ive seen the first Jon Wick, but not the second.  How was it>
I was not too fond of the second. The first one was amazing; the 2nd was way overdone
I loved all of the drama and suspense in the first
Really? There wasnt drama and suspense in the second one?
There was, but it felt fake. It was TOO over the top. I think they should of left it alone after the first
Keanu Reeves is amazing though
Yeah, I dig Keanu.  What was the plot of the second?

The bad guys in the first were not seeking revenge. Then there was a worldwide hit put out on him, and every single person who tried to take him out, John Wick killed. Awesome concept, but too much like a superhero type of a movie
Sounds like something I would like though.  Were there any other good actors in it?
Ruby Rose, Ian McShane.. You should probably check it out to see.. I think they are making a 3rd one too
I love Ruby Rose.  Does she make it til the end? Is she a good or bad guy?
She was one of the bad guys, against him.. She did make it to the end but...... You won't be seeing her in the 3rd, haha
Aww boo! I still think it sounds good.  Hate you didnt like it though.  I assume since theres a third being made that John makes it, though.  Are there some pretty gnarly fight scenes?
The first one was directed by Chad Stahelski, he's a great director
Yeah the fight scenes in both movies are pretty amazing
the effects in the 2nd are much more intense than the firs
t
Did he direct the second one also?
Yes he did!
I love the concept of the ex-hitman
I was so sad when his dog died in the original
Nice! I hate it when different directors do the second movie.  It never has the same feel.  Does John get a love interest in the movie>
Yes he did! :)
Oh yeah.  I hated the dog dying :(
Aww good! I didn't like seeing him so sad
I know. He's a good guy at heart
with bad on the outside, haha
So there was a hit put out on him just because he got out of the hitman business?
Yeah totally!
Yes he wanted to retire, and I don't think they liked that so much. They needed him
No one is better than John Wick! haha
As much as the world could NEED a hitman....lol
Thats the truth, lol!
It sounds like an interesting take.  Almost like a gang affiliation where youre in for lfe and the only way to get out is death.
I think in the first one, his wife died, which made him turn into something more evil
yes thats a really good analysis of it

uid2response.feedback: THIS ONE WENT MUCH BETTER THAN OTHERS I HAVE DONE BEFORE.  THE OTHER PATICIPANT ANSWERED MY QUESTIONS AND WAS VERY RECEPTIVE AND GAVE GREAT DETAIL.  ALTHOUGH THEY WERENT A FAN OF THE MOVIE, THE DETAILS THEY GAVE ME MADE ME WANT TO SEE IT.
